// Compact footer: a single row combining the tab list with a live mode
// indicator (NORMAL / TMUX / RESIZE / SESSION / ...).
//
// Why compact-bar instead of status-bar: the full status-bar renders a
// multi-line keybinding hint panel derived from the config. With this
// prefix-based setup it splashes the no-prefix Alt bindings — which on macOS
// do nothing unless the terminal sends Option as Meta, and read as a dead,
// mislabeled "Alt + <arrows>" footer (macOS has Option ⌥, not Alt). compact-bar
// keeps the useful mode indicator but drops that misleading hint dump.
//
// Discoverability is preserved by keys that work on EVERY platform with zero
// setup: the Ctrl+a prefix, F1, or Ctrl+a then ? — all open the cheatsheet.
layout {
    default_tab_template {
        children
        pane size=1 borderless=true {
            plugin location="zellij:compact-bar"
        }
    }
}
